                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-63079"><name nymRef="#Ἀριστίππα">Ἀριστίππα</name></persName>
                    <lb n="2"/><gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="line"/>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p>
                    <app loc="2"><note>no lost line mentioned in <bibl><ptr target="#SECir"/>, <citedRange>178</citedRange></bibl></note></app>
                </p>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p>Aristippa <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p>Aristippa <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p>Aristippa <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>The dowel hole is at such a place that the block might have belonged to a larger monument along with at least one similar block to its left.
                If so, another name might have stood on the other block.</p>
	      <p>With such a fragmentary context it is impossible to know whether Aristippa took part in a dedication or was honored with a statue.</p>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
